- Not the six-year-old,
the eight-year-old.

02:12.834 --> 02:14.041
- How are you not in prison?

02:14.041 --> 02:15.542
- Come on. It's art.

02:15.542 --> 02:16.625
- Or evidence.

02:16.625 --> 02:18.083
- Picture's up.

02:18.083 --> 02:19.875
- All right,
got to go be somewhat amusing.

02:19.875 --> 02:20.917
Can I leave this here?

02:20.917 --> 02:22.125
- No.

02:22.125 --> 02:24.583
Please take your twat and go.

02:24.583 --> 02:25.917
- [scoffs]

02:25.917 --> 02:27.750
Hey, check it out.
My kid did this.

02:27.750 --> 02:29.834
- You know
what really bothers me?

02:29.834 --> 02:32.083
- Besides the eight-year-old
drawing beaver shots?

02:32.083 --> 02:34.583
- You notice he wasn't
the least bit interested

02:34.583 --> 02:36.458
in our thing.

02:36.458 --> 02:38.959
- Well, I've got to say,
a set model versus kiddie porn?

02:38.959 --> 02:40.500
- No, that's not the point.

02:40.500 --> 02:43.125
If it's not about him,
he couldn't care less.

02:43.125 --> 02:45.709
- Right, he's self-involved.
He's narcissistic.

02:45.709 --> 02:46.500
He's...
[gasps]

02:46.500 --> 02:47.875
an actor.

02:47.875 --> 02:49.291
I know it's hard to remember

02:49.291 --> 02:50.792
given his work on this show.

02:50.792 --> 02:53.333
- Just so bloody one-sided.

02:53.333 --> 02:56.083
You realize he's never even
asked to read our script?

02:56.083 --> 02:57.959
Everyone in town has read it.

02:57.959 --> 03:00.500
Wouldn't you think
he'd be slightly curious?

03:00.500 --> 03:02.125
- Maybe he read it
and didn't like it.

03:02.125 --> 03:04.375
Maybe he's just trying
to spare our feelings.

03:04.375 --> 03:06.375
- Does that sound like him?
- Mm.

03:06.375 --> 03:09.083
Well, then, if he doesn't want
to read it, who cares?

03:09.083 --> 03:11.625
What, you need
his informed literary opinion?

03:11.625 --> 03:12.959
- No, it's just--

03:12.959 --> 03:15.125
- Who he is.

03:15.125 --> 03:17.458
Please let it go.

03:17.458 --> 03:21.125
Just compliment his son's vagina
and leave it at that.

03:26.792 --> 03:29.709
- So we, um--

03:29.709 --> 03:32.500
we have our first notes
on the script for the new show.

03:32.500 --> 03:33.834
- Yeah?
- Mm.

03:33.834 --> 03:35.667
It's amazing.
Virtually nothing.

03:35.667 --> 03:38.208
- Wow.

03:38.208 --> 03:42.083
- It's a little disconcerting,
all this unbridled praise.

03:42.083 --> 03:43.792
Everyone just seems to love it.

03:43.792 --> 03:45.166
- That's great.

03:45.166 --> 03:48.041
I'm thinking of getting a drone.
- A drone?

03:48.041 --> 03:49.333
- Yeah, anyone can buy them now.

03:49.333 --> 03:50.750
- What would you do
with a drone?

03:50.750 --> 03:53.041
- I don't know, drone stuff.

03:53.041 --> 03:54.834
Look at the tops of birds,

03:54.834 --> 03:56.166
see my roof,

03:56.166 --> 03:58.208
drop shit
on Burt Bacharach's house.

03:58.208 --> 04:01.000
- Why Burt Bacharach?
- It's a whole thing.

04:01.000 --> 04:04.917
But he'll know.

04:04.917 --> 04:07.333
- So you haven't by any chance
read it, have you?

04:07.333 --> 04:08.667
- What?

04:08.667 --> 04:09.917
- Our script.
- No.

04:09.917 --> 04:11.542
- Oh, good.

04:11.542 --> 04:13.875
For a second, I was afraid
you might be the one person

04:13.875 --> 04:15.875
who read it
and didn't love it.

04:15.875 --> 04:18.542
- Oh, not to worry.

04:18.542 --> 04:20.333
I could take pictures
of Suzanne Somers.

04:20.333 --> 04:21.834
- What?
- With my drone.

04:21.834 --> 04:23.375
She lives next to me.

04:23.375 --> 04:27.250
Her gardener told my gardener
that she lies out naked.

04:27.250 --> 04:29.583
I'd drone that.
- Right.

04:29.583 --> 04:32.000
[exhales]

04:32.000 --> 04:33.041
Quick question.
- Hmm?

04:33.041 --> 04:34.875
- What is wrong with you?

04:34.875 --> 04:36.500
Why don't you want to read it?
- What?

04:36.500 --> 04:39.709
- Our script.
Why don't you want to read it?

04:39.709 --> 04:41.500
- Whoa, okay, fine.
I'll read it.

04:41.500 --> 04:42.875
- Oh, no,
don't do me any favors.

04:42.875 --> 04:44.834
I don't need a mercy read.

04:44.834 --> 04:47.041
- All right.

04:47.041 --> 04:49.458
- Seriously?
You're not gonna read it?

04:49.458 --> 04:51.250
- Okay, I don't know
what you want here.

04:51.250 --> 04:53.959
- I would like, just for once,
for you to be interested

04:53.959 --> 04:56.125
in something
that's important to me.

04:56.125 --> 04:57.709
- Shouldn't we be
sleeping together

04:57.709 --> 04:58.834
to be having this conversation?

04:58.834 --> 05:00.417
- Fine.

05:02.250 --> 05:04.583
- [exhales]
Please can I read your script?

05:04.583 --> 05:05.750
- No.

05:05.750 --> 05:07.083
- You're right. I'm sorry.

05:07.083 --> 05:09.625
I'm a selfish asshole.
- Agreed.

05:09.625 --> 05:11.917
- I really want to read it.

05:11.917 --> 05:14.250
- Really?
- Yes.

05:16.667 --> 05:18.583
- All right.

05:18.583 --> 05:19.875
As long as you're not doing it

05:19.875 --> 05:21.417
just because I pressured you
into it.

05:21.417 --> 05:22.875
- Oh, well...
- What?

05:22.875 --> 05:26.417
- I'm kidding. Jesus.

05:26.417 --> 05:29.417
And by the way,
I know I don't say it enough,

05:29.417 --> 05:32.417
but you're the prettiest girl
in the room.

05:36.834 --> 05:39.583
Yeah, that's gonna be on TMZ.

05:39.583 --> 05:41.625
[keys clacking]

05:41.625 --> 05:44.417
- Where are we
on the Angry Men  rewrite?

05:44.417 --> 05:47.083
- I think some of them
are still too angry.

05:47.083 --> 05:50.125
- [sighs]
Is he ever gonna get there?

05:50.125 --> 05:51.875
Should we just pull the plug
on this thing?

05:51.875 --> 05:53.792
- Probably.
I don't think he's capab--

