06:32.291 --> 06:35.166
- Carol, Helen needs to see you.

06:35.166 --> 06:36.875
- Okay.

06:36.875 --> 06:38.166
Right back.

06:52.458 --> 06:53.500
- Morning.

06:53.500 --> 06:54.542
- Hey.

07:01.542 --> 07:02.917
- How was your weekend?

07:02.917 --> 07:04.792
- Eh, quiet.

07:08.709 --> 07:10.291
- What did you do?

07:10.291 --> 07:11.959
- Nothing, really.

07:11.959 --> 07:15.542
Hung out, watched TV.

07:17.375 --> 07:19.041
- Read anything?

07:19.041 --> 07:20.875
- Actually, I'm reading
this book on tape.

07:20.875 --> 07:22.417
It's really cool.

07:22.417 --> 07:24.291
It's about how
if Hitler had won the war--

07:24.291 --> 07:25.917
I'll tell you,
we sure dodged a bullet there.

07:25.917 --> 07:27.208
[chuckles]

07:31.208 --> 07:33.208
What?

07:40.291 --> 07:42.750
Oh! Oh, oh, right.
- Right.

07:42.750 --> 07:44.959
- I'm gonna get to it
as soon as I get a free minute.

07:44.959 --> 07:46.542
- You had
the whole bloody weekend.

07:46.542 --> 07:47.542
- I said I'll read it.

07:47.542 --> 07:49.792
- It's 28 pages.

07:49.792 --> 07:51.667
It's not the fucking Goldfinch.

07:51.667 --> 07:54.083
- I don't know--
- It's a thick book.

07:54.083 --> 07:56.000
- Got you.
- Unbelievable.

08:00.709 --> 08:03.291
- Knock, knock.
What's up?

08:03.291 --> 08:07.375
- I believe there is something
for you on my desk.

08:07.375 --> 08:09.583
- What is this?

08:09.583 --> 08:10.792
What did you do?

08:10.792 --> 08:12.291
- Open it.

08:12.291 --> 08:15.750
- [sighs]
You should not have done this.

08:15.750 --> 08:16.750
[chuckles]

08:18.959 --> 08:21.875
Oh, my God.

08:21.875 --> 08:24.500
This is--

08:26.250 --> 08:29.000
No one has ever--

08:29.000 --> 08:31.291
I can't even--

08:31.291 --> 08:33.667
I can't--

08:33.667 --> 08:35.250
I can't--

08:35.250 --> 08:36.959
I can't breathe.

08:36.959 --> 08:38.834
- Calm down.
You're breathing.

08:38.834 --> 08:40.125
- A key?

08:40.125 --> 08:41.417
After two weeks?

08:41.417 --> 08:44.458
It's just--
it's too much too fast.

08:44.458 --> 08:46.291
Oh, did I tell you?

08:46.291 --> 08:48.625
She already invited me
to Stanford

08:48.625 --> 08:50.083
for her daughter's graduation.

08:50.083 --> 08:51.959
- Aw.
- In June.

08:51.959 --> 08:53.458
- Well, that's not so--

08:53.458 --> 08:55.959
- No, not this June.
Next June.

08:55.959 --> 08:58.500
- Oh.
- Oh, God.

08:58.500 --> 09:01.208
What is wrong with me?

09:01.208 --> 09:03.166
I should be happy.

09:03.166 --> 09:06.083
This--
it's like a dream come true,

09:06.083 --> 09:07.959
and I'm getting hives.

09:07.959 --> 09:10.166
- Oh,
that is definitely hive-y.

09:10.166 --> 09:11.500
- All right, stop looking.

09:11.500 --> 09:12.750
- Okay. Okay, listen.

09:12.750 --> 09:16.542
You have to tell her
how you feel.

09:16.542 --> 09:18.291
- Nyeh.

09:18.291 --> 09:21.458
- You can't spend an entire
relationship on antihistamines.

09:21.458 --> 09:23.709
- Wh-what am I supposed to say?

09:23.709 --> 09:25.083
"Less love, please."

09:25.083 --> 09:28.542
I--I don't want to hurt her.

09:28.542 --> 09:31.500
- You're just asking her
to slow down a bit.

09:31.500 --> 09:35.291
Look, if this relationship
has any hope of sustaining,

09:35.291 --> 09:37.750
you have got to be honest.

09:37.750 --> 09:40.166
- Okay, fine.

09:40.166 --> 09:41.625
[sighs]
You're right.

09:41.625 --> 09:42.792
I hear you.

09:42.792 --> 09:46.917
[cell phone ringing]

09:46.917 --> 09:48.250
Yeah.

09:48.250 --> 09:50.500
[stammering]

09:50.500 --> 09:52.542
Hi, sweetie.

09:52.542 --> 09:54.041
No, I'm at the dentist.

09:54.041 --> 09:56.417
I lost a crown.

09:56.417 --> 09:58.750
It's all good.
Be back soon.

09:58.750 --> 10:00.709
[whimpers]
I got to go.

10:07.291 --> 10:08.959
- You know, I'm a writer too.

10:08.959 --> 10:11.709
- Oh, no. No, I did not.

10:11.709 --> 10:13.709
- I'm working on a screenplay.

10:13.709 --> 10:15.000
- Ah.

10:15.000 --> 10:16.583
Oh, good for you.

10:19.542 --> 10:20.750
- It's about this girl.

10:20.750 --> 10:22.333
- Oh, okay.

10:22.333 --> 10:23.709
- Nobody ever notices her.

10:23.709 --> 10:26.667
No one ever asks about her life
or how she's doing.

10:26.667 --> 10:29.417
It's--it's like
she's not a person too.

10:29.417 --> 10:30.834
No one cares.
- Aw.

10:30.834 --> 10:34.792
- So she decides to kill
her coworkers.

10:36.750 --> 10:39.166
- Ah.
Did not see that coming.

10:39.166 --> 10:40.750
There's your twist.

10:40.750 --> 10:45.166
- She just feels like,
"You don't notice me?

10:45.166 --> 10:46.500
You'll notice me."

10:46.500 --> 10:49.166
- And there's your motivation.

10:49.166 --> 10:51.083
Good, you'll need that.

10:51.083 --> 10:55.375
So...
she kills them...

10:55.375 --> 10:57.333
- By poisoning them.

10:57.333 --> 10:59.583
- I see.

10:59.583 --> 11:02.250
- She does it slowly,
little by little,

11:02.250 --> 11:05.041
and no one suspects
because she's just this girl.

11:05.041 --> 11:07.500
Who is she?
She's nobody.

11:07.500 --> 11:08.625
No one would think.

11:08.625 --> 11:10.667
- Of course not.
Perfect crime.

11:10.667 --> 11:12.166
- Can I show it to you
when I'm done?

11:12.166 --> 11:14.583
- Absolutely.
Yes, I'm very interested.

11:14.583 --> 11:17.291
[chuckling]

11:23.458 --> 11:24.375
Where did you get that?

11:24.375 --> 11:26.250
- Over there.

11:26.250 --> 11:28.041
What are you doing?
- Nothing.

11:30.000 --> 11:32.917
- Fucking brilliant.

11:32.917 --> 11:34.166
- You read it?

11:34.166 --> 11:36.166
- Like I had a choice.
- Interesting.

11:36.166 --> 11:41.125
- Oh, well,
I might have mentioned once or--

11:41.125 --> 11:42.667
stop looking at me.

11:42.667 --> 11:44.750
- It is so good.
- Really?

11:44.750 --> 11:46.458
- Oh, my God.
I laughed my ass off.

11:46.458 --> 11:48.041
Now I see why
everybody's flipping out.

11:48.041 --> 11:49.375
- Thank you.
- My goodness.

11:49.375 --> 11:51.250
- So have you started casting?

11:51.250 --> 11:52.667
Can I put in a good word
for someone?

11:52.667 --> 11:53.834
- Absolutely. Who?

11:53.834 --> 11:55.041
- Me.

11:57.542 --> 11:58.542
- I'm sorry?
- Say what?

11:58.542 --> 12:01.875
- I would love to do this.

12:04.667 --> 12:06.834
- Great.

12:07.834 --> 12:09.917
- Yes, great.

12:09.917 --> 12:13.750
What, um--
what part were you thinking?

12:13.750 --> 12:15.417
- Well, got to be Anderson.

12:15.417 --> 12:17.333
It's like you wrote it for me.

12:17.333 --> 12:20.041
- Not really.
[chuckling]

12:20.041 --> 12:23.625
Y-you should know
that the actor playing Anderson

12:23.625 --> 12:27.625
also has to play Riggs,
so that's maybe more than you--

12:27.625 --> 12:29.417
- Holy shit, I love Riggs.
- Oh.

12:29.417 --> 12:31.583
- That's my second favorite.

12:31.583 --> 12:34.041
So I'm Anderson and Riggs?

12:34.041 --> 12:36.875
- Apparently so.
- Wow.

12:36.875 --> 12:39.458
I got to tell you,
I was so scared

12:39.458 --> 12:42.250
I'd get stuck taking
some shit show for the check,

12:42.250 --> 12:44.041
but this?

12:44.041 --> 12:46.250
And with you guys?

12:46.250 --> 12:48.834
I--I don't know what to say.

12:48.834 --> 12:51.792
- I think we're all at a loss.
[both chuckle]

12:51.792 --> 12:53.834
- All right.
I got to call my agent.

12:53.834 --> 12:55.709
Let's get this thing going.
Whoo-hoo!

12:55.709 --> 12:57.542
- Whoo-hoo.

13:00.875 --> 13:02.542
Why did you say "great"?

13:02.542 --> 13:04.959
- Well, you said "great."
- Only because you said it.

13:04.959 --> 13:07.458
